{% import '_templates/component/components.njk' as components %}

    {% call components.section("Overview") -%}
      <p>A tooltip is a user-triggered floating text area that provides helpful or contextual information.</p>
    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Sample component") -%}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-sample.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component sample" style="--inline-img-max-width: 264px;">
    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Component status") -%}
      <rhds-component-status component="Tooltip"></rhds-component-status>
    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Style") -%}

    <p>A tooltip can be placed on a light or dark background. It consists of text wrapped in a container that sometimes includes a subtle drop shadow. The container also includes an arrow that points to a <em>Help</em> or <em>Information</em> icon.</p>

    <div class="margin-top--4">
      {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
        <div class="margin-top--4 centered margin-bottom--4">
          <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-style.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component style" style="--inline-img-max-width: 320px;">
        </div>
      {%- endcall %}
    </div>

    <h4>Light theme</h4>
      {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-light-theme.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component, light theme" style="--example-img-max-width: 264px;">
      {%- endcall %}

    <h4>Dark theme</h4>
      {% call components.example(palette='darkest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-dark-theme.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component, dark theme" style="--example-img-max-width: 264px;">
      {%- endcall %}

    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Usage") -%}

    <h4>Content</h4>
    <p>Content in a tooltip is limited to text only and should be brief and helpful to a user. If content needs to be more thorough or interactive elements need to be included, use a <a href="../popover" target="_blank">Popover</a> or <a href="../modal" target="_blank">Modal</a> instead.</p>

    <h4>Icon pairing</h4>
    <p>A tooltip should always be paired with a <em>Help</em> or <em>Information</em> icon, or be connected to a link or other component.</p>

    <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
     {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-icon-pairing.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component icon pairing" style="--inline-img-max-width: 566px;">
     {%- endcall %}
    </div>

    <h4>Orientations</h4>
    <p>Depending on the amount of content or available screen space, a tooltip can be used in different orientations. There is no default, but when choosing an orientation, be mindful of how a tooltip can potentially cover up important content or get cut off by the browser window.</p>

    <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
      {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-orientations.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component orientations" style="--inline-img-max-width: 676px;">
     {%- endcall %}
    </div>

    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

    <p>How a user interacts with a tooltip depends on what the screen size is.</p>

    <ul>
     <li>On large screens, a tooltip disappears after a user moves their cursor off of the icon</li>
     <li>On large screens, a tooltip disappears after the focus indicator is moved away from the icon</li>
     <li>On small screens, a tooltip disappears after a user taps the icon again or taps outside of the tooltip</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
     {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-behavior.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component behavior" style="--inline-img-max-width: 500px;">
     {%- endcall %}
      </div>

    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Responsive design") -%}

    <p>A tooltip can work on both large and small screens, depending on the amount of content or available screen space.</p>

    <h4>Breakpoints</h4>
    <p>A tooltip mostly remains the same on large and small screens.</p>

    <h4>Large screens</h4>
    <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-responsive-large-screens.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component responsive design, large screens">

    <h4>Small screens</h4>
    <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-responsive-small-screens.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component responsive design, small screens" style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">

    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Interaction states") -%}

    <p>The only interaction state is appearing next to an icon when focused, hovered, or tapped.</p>

    <div class="margin-top--4 margin-bottom--4">
      {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-interaction-states.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component interaction states, hovered or tapped" style="--inline-img-max-width: 592px;">
      {%- endcall %}
    </div>

    <p class="footnote" style="margin-top:-3rem; letter-spacing: 0.2px;">A tooltip can appear when hovered or tapped</p>

    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Best practices") -%}

    <h4>Accessibility</h4>
    <p>For better accessibility, do not use a light tooltip in a light environment because it will blend into the background too much.</p>

    {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
      <div class="inline-flex centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-best-practice-1.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component best practice 1" style="--inline-img-max-width: 264px;">
      </div>
    {%- endcall %}

    <h4>Orientation</h4>
    <p>Content inside of a tooltip should not be cut off by the browser window, change the tooltip orientation if it does.</p>

    {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
      <div class="inline-flex centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-best-practice-2.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component best practice 2" style="--inline-img-max-width: 360px;">
      </div>
    {%- endcall %}

    <h4>Pairing</h4>
    <p>Do not add a tooltip to things that do not require further explanation, like simple links and components.</p>

    {% call components.example(palette='wrong') %}
      <div class="inline-flex centered">
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-best-practice-3.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component best practice 3" style="--inline-img-max-width: 170px;">
      </div>
    {%- endcall %}

    {%- endcall %}

    {% call components.section("Spacing") -%}

      <p>A tooltip uses <a href="https://www.patternfly.org/v4/guidelines/spacers">PatternFly 4 spacers</a> to define spacing values between elements. Every tooltip orientation contains the same amount of container padding and exterior spacing in between the arrow and icon.</p>

      {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-spacing-light-theme.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component spacing, light theme" style="--example-img-max-width: 264px;">
      {%- endcall %}

      {% call components.example(palette='darkest') %}
        <img src="{{ '/assets/tooltip/tooltip-spacing-dark-theme.svg' | url }}" alt="Tooltip component spacing, dark theme" style="--example-img-max-width: 264px;">
      {%- endcall %}

    {%- endcall %}

